Date: Sun 1 Dec 2002 3:03 PM
From: "Matthias Borchert" <Matthias.Borchert@lshtm.ac.uk>

I re-read my message [ref. (02) below] and discovered a small error. It
should read:
"All 7 are alive, and their blood samples tested negative at NIV for Ebola
and Marburg by PCR." - instead of "All 6...".
Neither the 6 suspect cases from Doruma nor the one from Dungu were real VHF
[viral hemorrhagic fever] cases.
--
Matthias Borchert MD MSc
