<matthias.borchert@lshtm.ac.uk>
[Re: "real VHF cases", I suppose they were all clinically compatible with
VHF, it's just that the actual etiological agent couldnÂ´t be identified.
This could be due to one or more of several factors, ranging from the only
blood specimen available being in poor condition, or taken after the end of
viremia & before a rise in antibody titer, to it being a new microbial
agent. - Mod.JW]
